So I had a bit of a last minute #Halloween costume panic and decided to go as a bee but somehow the costume my friend Megan picked out gave everyone the impression that I was dressed up as the Blind Melon Bee Girl even though if you actually Google "Blind Melon Bee Girl" I look completely different. Fine. Whatever. I'm rolling with it. So I'm walking to this house party by myself through my super hip neighborhood dressed as not the Blind Melon Bee Girl and I stop at this liquor store on the way because tequila is the only thing that makes the pain go away and these two drunk guys are leaving the store as I come in and one goes "Blind Melon" and I'm like "yeah you got it" and they leave and I go to buy the booze and the one guy comes back in and he's like "Hey!" And I'm like "Huh?" And he's like "My best friend's sister!" And I'm like "What?" And he goes "My best friend's sister!" And I'm like "yeah?" And he goes "She's the bee" and I'm like "wait, the Blind Melon bee?" And he's like "yeah!" And I go "holy shit!" And he goes "I know!" And I say "well, how's she doing?" And he goes "she's doing great!" And I say "tell her she's an inspiration to me!" And he says "I will!"... And that's how I know that @ElonMusk is right and we're all just living inside some insane computer simulation.
.
.
Anyway, at the end of the night I realized I never got a picture of my full costume so thank you to the very kind 7-Eleven employee who was nice enough to take this photo of me at 330 in the morning. Happy Halloween!

#tbt to having dinner in #MexicoCity with these fools. Funny story: While we were shooting #ConanMexico, we were staying in the same hotel as #JustinBieber - so the entire week, there were hundreds of screaming Justin Bieber fans waiting outside the front of our hotel day and night. Our crew would travel in a caravan of black SUVs, and every night we would pull up to the front of the hotel after a long day of shooting and be met by hundreds of screaming girls who all thought we were @JustinBieber. They would go absolutely nuts; screaming, waving signs, jumping up and down, the whole thing. Then, of course, we would get out - and 300 teenage girls would all make a disappointed "AWWW" at the same time. Their sadness was deafening, and it happened EVERY. SINGLE. NIGHT. It was hilarious. Anyway, thanks for the grub, boss.

My great great grandpa fought for the North in some of the bloodiest battles of the Civil War. So bloody, in fact, that everybody in his company kept dying so he kept getting reassigned to different campaigns. (This is his discharge letter that details all the battles he fought in, from the Stone River Campaign, to the Chickamunga Campaign, to the Siege of Chattanooga, to the Battle of Peachtree Creek & Sherman's Atlanta campaign.) Thanks for surviving, gramps - and thank you to all those who have put themselves in harm's way in service to our country. Happy #MemorialDay!

So I won a shitload of money at craps then came up to my room to shower and saw two girls struggling with putting a box on a rolling bag. Without thinking, I run down the hallway to help - only to realize they are SUPREMELY fucked up and are basically just trying to take a shitload of alcohol to another room. The one girl is eating pizza, and the other girl has smashed a beer bottle on the floor and neither one of them are having an easy time standing up. I help them balance the box on the rolling bag, then the one girl is like "omg thanks so much kind stranger" and rolls the bag away over her slice of pizza. I look down to the pizza, which has a bunch of blood on it, then look at my hand which I realize is COVERED in blood because the girl had sliced her hand open and didn't realize it. I go into my room, wash off the blood, take a shower, and get ready for tonight. I come back out, 45 MINUTES LATER, to find the box at the end of the hall, MORE smashed bottles, and THE SAME TWO FUCKING GIRLS BY THE ELEVATOR. They're trying to get the booze on the elevator, STILL, and the other girl has wrapped her bloody hand in a rag. They are ecstatic to see me. I tell them to, "FOR THE LOVE OF GOD JUST MAKE TWO TRIPS" and this blows their fucking minds, and then I take the elevator down to the lobby and out of their lives forever. Alcohol: it's a hell of a drug. #Vegas

So when you get nominated for an Emmy they invite you to this nomination ceremony thing with all the other nominees and there's food and free drinks and they put on a little show and all this other fun stuff happens and at the end they give you this nomination certificate and you get to get your photo taken with the governor and everything. So anyway, this one year I was really into this bit where for the entire year I insisted every single photo taken of me was one of me weeping profusely because I thought it was really funny for some reason (I'm weird), and so at the nomination ceremony I made this nice and extremely professional photographer take a photo of the governor and myself weeping while holding my nomination certificate because, let's be honest, there was no way on God's green earth that I was going to win an actual Emmy so why not have a little fun with the whole thing, right? Right. So flash forward a few weeks and I actually win the stupid Emmy - and it's crazy and I'm overwhelmed and extremely grateful and I go up onstage and blurt out a hasty thanks and babble a few words that I can't remember and then go backstage and suddenly LL Cool J is giving me a high five and chanting "Team Coco, baby Team Coco baby" and all these very intense interviews happen in front of all these very bright lights and it's all so quick I'm trying to be funny but I have no idea what I'm saying to all these people and then they shuffle me over to this table where there are like a thousand Emmys and I have to sign for mine and they hand it over and I make a hood ornament joke that no one thinks is funny before being led on to this step & repeat where they're going to take my photo with my big golden statuette and right as I go to smile the photographer stops and goes "wait, aren't you the guy who only cries in photos?" and I realize it's THE SAME PHOTOGRAPHER FROM BEFORE and we both laughed and it suddenly struck me how completely weird and insane life can be and anyway that's how I ended up getting this photo of me holding my Emmy and crying. #tbt #Emmys
